To create the dependency tree for the given Swedish sentence "Därför genmodifierar vi växterna dvs, man ändrar på växternas gener för att få fram den växt med de egenskaper man söker.", we break it down as follows:

1. Därför (therefore) - adverb, modifies the main verb.
2. genmodifierar (genetically modify) - verb, the main action.
3. vi (we) - subject of the verb.
4. växterna (the plants) - object of the verb (definite form).
5. dvs (that is) - discourse marker, can be treated like a conjunction in this context.
6. man (one/people) - subject of a following verb.
7. ändrar (changes) - verb, the main action related to 'man'.
8. på (on/about) - preposition.
9. växternas (the plants') - possessive form, relates to 'gener'.
10. gener (genes) - object of the preposition.
11. för (to) - preposition, introduces an infinitival clause.
12. att (to) - infinitive marker.
13. få (get) - infinitive verb.
14. fram (forward) - particle, modifies 'få'.
15. den (the) - definite article, modifies 'växt'.
16. växt (plant) - head noun of the phrase.
17. med (with) - preposition, introduces details about 'växt'.
18. de (the) - definite article, modifies 'egenskaper'.
19. egenskaper (properties) - object of the preposition.
20. man (one/people) - subject of the verb in the subordinate clause.
21. söker (seeks) - verb in the subordinate clause.

